    "text": "This data can't rule injury in or out, but the recovery drop lines up with a normal response to novel, heavy strength work rather than proving something broke. A drop from 71% to 48% overnight has three visible contributors. First, yesterday's session itself: 58 min at a training load of 16.8, with effort logged as 8 of 10 — the hardest lifting in your recent history. Second, HRV at 46 ms, down from a 30-day baseline of 52.3 ms; heavy loading often lines up with a short HRV dip while soreness resolves. Third, a short night: 6.6 h against your 7.4 h need. The read is conditional, not a verdict: if HRV and resting heart rate drift back toward baseline over the next couple of days and no sharp or worsening pain appears, this fits adaptation cost. Tonight's lever: choose easy movement tomorrow rather than round two.",
